DocumentName: dicom-fuzzer 1.11.0 (manual SBOM)
DocumentNamespace: https://example.invalid/dicom-fuzzer-1.11.0/manual
Creator: Tool: hand-curated
Creator: Person: David Dashti
Created: 2026-05-09T00:00:00Z
DocumentComment: <text>Hand-curated SBOM for dicom-fuzzer 1.11.0. Models the
FDA-curator philosophy: comprehensive enough on its own to meet NTIA
minimum baseline for shipped components, plus vendored entries only a
hand-curated SBOM can record (statically linked codec, vendored zlib).
Dev/test tooling (pytest, ruff, mypy, pre-commit, type stubs, packaging
machinery) is intentionally excluded because it does not ship with the
product; Syft picks those up from the venv and they land in the report's
only-in-Syft bucket as expected. Two entries (cffi, packaging) are one
minor behind the Syft view to exercise the version_mismatches bucket;
click intentionally disagrees with Syft on license to exercise the
license_mismatches bucket. See docs/WORKFLOW.md for the curator's
full guide.</text>

